Subset of the output differentiated by diaganosis
```{r}
MEL<-subset(output,Label == "MEL")
NEV<-subset(output, Label == "NEV")
SEK<-subset(output, Label == "SEK")
```




Symmetry:
```{r}
mean(MEL$Symmetry)
sd(MEL$Symmetry)
```

```{r}
NEV_mean<-mean(NEV$Symmetry)
NEV_sd<-sd(NEV$Symmetry)
print(NEV_mean)
print(NEV_sd)
```


```{r}
SEK_mean<-mean(SEK$Symmetry)
SEK_sd<-sd(SEK$Symmetry)
print(SEK_mean)
print(SEK_sd)
```


```{r}
t.test(NEV$Symmetry,SEK$Symmetry)
```
